# Portfolio Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- Framework: Astro (static site generator) with React islands for interactive components
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4 (via @tailwindcss/vite plugin)
- Icons: Lucide-React
- Language: TypeScript (strict mode)
- Deployment: GitHub Pages via GitHub Actions

## Project Structure
- `src/pages/` — Astro pages (file-based routing)
- `src/layouts/` — Shared layout templates (`.astro`)
- `src/components/` — Reusable components (`.astro` for static, `.tsx` for interactive)
- `src/styles/global.css` — Tailwind entry point
- `public/` — Static assets (images, fonts, favicon)

## Coding Standards
- Use `.astro` components for static content (default — ships zero JS).
- Use `.tsx` React components ONLY when client-side interactivity is needed (e.g., Nav toggle, modals).
- Always add `client:load` or `client:visible` directive when using React components in Astro pages.
- Use functional components with TypeScript.
- Favor semantic HTML (e.g., `<header>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<footer>`).
- Ensure all images have descriptive `alt` tags for accessibility.
- Use Tailwind's utility classes for all styling; avoid writing custom CSS files unless absolutely necessary.
- Keep components small and modular (e.g., separate Nav, Hero, ProjectCard, and Footer).

## Design Preferences
- Modern, clean, and minimalist aesthetic.
- Responsive design is a priority (mobile-first approach).
- Use a consistent color palette (recommend a dark/light mode toggle).
- Dark theme base: zinc-950 background, zinc-100 text, blue-600 accent.

## Project Context
- My Name: Twan Grooff
- Role: Robotics engineer / Software engineer
- Goal: Showcase projects to recruiters and highlight technical skills.
